      "content": "but you're being too \"supportive\" and not being logical. if we look at it strictly from a probability or utility standpoint, the cost of living is constant and high, while the \"meaning\" is zero or unproven. so logically, a neutral state—non-existence—is actually a more efficient outcome than continuing to incur the cost for no gain. don't you see how that's just a rational conclusion?",
